    {
      "title": "[正面] Truly outstanding game. Haven't been too far in th...",
      "summary": "Truly outstanding game. Haven't been too far in the story yet, but already completely fell in love with the game and its story (currently just beat chapter 2)\r\n\r\nSTORY\r\nAbsolutely incredible. I usually skip stories in games, even games I usually wouldn't skip stories on, they just end up stretching for so long that I end up skipping them, but here I've yet to feel bored reading it.\r\n\r\nGRAPHICS\r\nIncredible graphics, however sad with how lacking the game is in transitions with its backgrounds, as each background is very well made, but still feels like a slideshow at times, same with the characters, they are very expressive, some seem to have many expressions, but the transitions between these are instant. \r\n\r\nAUDIO\r\nAbsolutely incredible audio and sound design, I could listen to Hymn of the Unveiling for hours on end, I always turn off my playlist (that I never turn off otherwise) when I play this game. The characters voicing sometimes do feel a little cheap, but still often work very good, I would love seeing more voicing tho.\r\n\r\nGAMEPLAY\r\nThe gameplay is fun, characters are all unique enough, with some being completely different from their own archetype, bringing spice to your team compositions, I was about to complain about just being able to do everything with a single team, but the game pushes (and sometimes forces) the player to use the different characters archetypes, which brings more gameplay variety.\r\n\r\nWHAT BRINGS THIS GAME DOWN\r\nThe game's mostly brought down by its poor and inconsistent translations, I've seen the English and French translations, the game is mostly unplayable on French, for example cards descriptions being wildly inconsistent with effect names, sometimes using completely wrong acronyms, or even having effects' brackets open, but never close etc...\r\nThe english translation is not great either, but is more than enough to understand everything that happens, and everything you can do\r\n\r\nOVERALL\r\nThe game runs great, both on PC and Mobile, the difficulty is progressive, but yet too low for me, being able to clear some level 30 challenge modes with a team of 1 level 20 and 3 level 10 characters.\r\nIf you like gachas, card based RPG and/or lovecraftian horrors, play this. Don't be like me and keep it on your \"may play later\" list for over a year.",
